# File Structure Convention

Canonical layout for everything under `src/`. Read before adding any file. The route-island skill ([`agent-os/skills/route-island/SKILL.md`](../skills/route-island/SKILL.md)) implements these rules step-by-step; this is the contract.

## Top-Level Layout

```
tests/                                  At project root: e2e/, load/, factories/, utils/
src/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ app/                                Application shell: route tree, guards, providers, error boundaries
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ core/                               Framework-agnostic services
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ pages/                              Page-first feature directories (each = a frontend route)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ shared/                             Cross-page reusables: components, forms, hooks, layouts, store
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ lib/                                Pure utilities (no side effects)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ App.tsx
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ main.tsx
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ index.css
```

**`src/core/`** is the irreducible platform kernel ‚Äî only framework-agnostic, app-state-free services: `http/`, `rbac/`, `config/`, `data-provider/`, `resources/`, `types/`, `version/`. **Anything app-shell-y, React-Provider-y, or app-state-dependent lives outside `core/`:**
- App-shell bootstrap (Sentry init, web-vitals, PostHog setup) ‚Üí **`src/app/`** (`app/analytics/`, `app/observability/`)
- Runtime infrastructure used by every layer (auth token + service, errors handling) ‚Üí **`src/shared/`** (`shared/auth/`, `shared/errors/`)
- Zustand client state ‚Üí **`src/shared/store/<X>Store/`** (folder-per-unit) ‚Äî all 5 stores including `useAuthStore` and `useTenantStore`
- Cross-page API helpers ‚Üí **`src/shared/api/`** (`organization-*`, `my-orgs`, `tenancy-service`)

## Naming ‚Äî three categories

### 1. Role files ‚Äî page-prefixed, lowercase-dotted

One per page. The prefix makes them globally unique ‚Üí AI agents, grep, and IDE quick-open all resolve without ambiguity.

| File | Required? | Purpose |
|------|-----------|---------|
| `<page>.route.tsx` | ‚úì | Lazy boundary (`Component`, `loader`, `ErrorBoundary`) |
| `<page>.page.ts` | ‚úì | Manifest: `path`, `testId`, `permission`, `kind`, `children` |
| `<page>.contracts.ts` | optional | Zod schemas + inferred TS types |
| `<page>.api.ts` | optional | Fetcher functions for this page |
| `<page>.search.ts` | optional | URL search-param schema (TanStack Router `validateSearch`) |
| `<page>.fixtures.ts` | optional | Mock generators (marked `REPLACE_WITH_API`) |
| `<page>.constants.ts` | optional | Page-scoped constants |
| `<page>.resource.ts` | resource pages only | Resource manifest (endpoint, schema, permissions) |

### 2. Identity files ‚Äî generic, uppercase

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `OVERVIEW.md` | AI/human entry doc ‚Äî first file an agent reads on this island |

### 3. UI files ‚Äî PascalCase

| File | When |
|------|------|
| `<Page>Page.tsx` | Top-level UI; manifest `kind: 'leaf'` |
| `<Page>Layout.tsx` | Top-level UI; manifest `kind: 'layout'` (mounts `<Outlet />`) |
| Sub-units in `components/`, `forms/`, `hooks/`, `dialogs/`, `store/` | See "Folder-per-unit" below |

## Folder-per-unit (components, forms, hooks, dialogs, store)

Every component / form / hook / dialog / store lives in its own folder with three files:

```
<Name>/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <Name>.tsx              source (or .ts for hooks/store)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <Name>.test.tsx         test (or .ts)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ index.ts                export { <Name> } from './<Name>.tsx';
```

Apply to:
- `components/<Name>/`
- `forms/<Name>Form/`
- `hooks/use<Name>/`
- `dialogs/<Name>Dialog/`
- `store/use<X>Store/`

**Sub-unit names are not page-prefixed** ‚Äî the path already provides context:
- ‚úì `pages/dashboard/components/ActivityFeed/`
- ‚úó `pages/dashboard/components/DashboardActivityFeed/`

**Exception ‚Äî shadcn primitives stay flat.** `src/shared/components/ui/` keeps the shadcn convention (`button.tsx`, `card.tsx`, etc.) ‚Äî no folder-per-unit. Other shared components follow folder-per-unit.

## Page Naming (directory)

| Pattern | Use for | Example |
|---------|---------|---------|
| **Plural noun** | Collection / list view | `pages/organizations/` ‚Üí `/organizations` |
| **Singular noun** | Single resource (current context) | `pages/organization/` ‚Üí `/organization` (user's current org) |
| **kebab-case verb-noun** | Action / workflow | `pages/create-organization/` ‚Üí `/create-organization` |
| **kebab-case noun** | Multi-word concept | `pages/accept-invite/` ‚Üí `/accept-invite` |

Page directory names are **lowercase kebab-case**. Sub-pages under a layout follow the same rules (`organization/sub-pages/api-keys/`, etc.).

## Two page shapes ‚Äî custom and resource

### Custom page

For pages that aren't a backend resource (dashboard, settings, auth, onboarding, accept-invite):

```
src/pages/<page>/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ OVERVIEW.md
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <page>.route.tsx
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <page>.page.ts
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <Page>Page.tsx | <Page>Layout.tsx
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <page>.contracts.ts                    if has data shapes
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <page>.api.ts                          if talks to backend
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <page>.search.ts                       if has URL search params
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <page>.fixtures.ts                     if mocked
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <page>.constants.ts                    optional
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ store/                                 RARE ‚Äî only when page-local UI state exists
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ use<X>Store/{use<X>Store.ts, use<X>Store.test.ts, index.ts}
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/<Name>/{...}                page-specific sub-widgets
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ forms/<Name>Form/{...}                 page-specific forms
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ hooks/use<Name>/{...}                  page-specific hooks (TanStack Query, etc.)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ __tests__/integration/                 cross-component flows in this island
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ sub-pages/<child>/                     nested route, full recursive copy
```

### Resource page

For pages that map to a backend resource (organizations, members, roles, invitations, api-keys, billing):

```
src/pages/<resource>/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ OVERVIEW.md
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <resource>.route.tsx                   parent route ‚Äî renders the list
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <resource>.page.ts                     kind: 'layout', children: ['create', '$id', '$id-edit']
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <resource>.resource.ts                 resource manifest (endpoint, schema, permissions)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <resource>.contracts.ts                Zod ‚Äî shared across all CRUD views
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <resource>.api.ts                      optional; most resources use shared CRUD hooks
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <Resource>ListPage.tsx                 top-level UI ‚Äî the list
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/<Name>/{...}                list widgets (Table, Filters, EmptyState)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ forms/<Name>Form/{...}                 reusable forms consumed by dialogs
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ dialogs/<Name>Dialog/{...}             URL-driven action dialogs
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ hooks/use<Name>/{...}                  resource-specific hooks (most use shared CRUD)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ sub-pages/                             URL-driven dialog placeholders (each renders null)
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ create/                            ‚Üí /<resource>/create
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ $id/                               ‚Üí /<resource>/[id]      (show)
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ $id-edit/                          ‚Üí /<resource>/[id]/edit (edit)
```

Resource pages use `<Resource>ListPage.tsx` (PascalCase, page-prefixed) as the top-level UI. The list page mounts the action dialogs and reads URL to open them.

## CRUD UX convention ‚Äî URL-driven dialogs

For resource pages, the standard mapping:

| Action | URL | Renders | Why URL? |
|--------|-----|---------|----------|
| **List** | `/<resource>` | Page | Destination; must be shareable |
| **Create** | `/<resource>/create` | Dialog over list | Refresh-safe, deep-linkable |
| **Show** | `/<resource>/[id]` | Page or dialog over list | Shareable detail link |
| **Edit** | `/<resource>/[id]/edit` | Dialog over list | Refresh-safe, deep-linkable; `[id]` loads the row |
| **Delete** | *(no URL)* | Inline `AlertDialog` confirm | Transient one-click destructive action |
| **Quick toggles** | *(no URL)* | Inline button / dropdown | Transient |

On disk, `[id]` is the folder `$id` (TanStack Router convention).

**Implementation pattern.** Parent `<Resource>ListPage.tsx` reads `useRouterState({ select: s => s.location.pathname })`, computes which dialog (if any) the URL implies, and renders it open. The list stays mounted behind the dialog backdrop.

**Forward compatibility ‚Äî promoting dialog ‚Üí full page.** When a Create/Edit dialog outgrows the modal (multi-step wizard, >15 fields, file uploads, shareable drafts):
1. URL stays the same (`/<resource>/create` or `/<resource>/[id]/edit`)
2. Replace the dialog mount in the list page with the sub-page's `route.tsx` rendering a full `<X>Page.tsx`
3. No URL break, no bookmark break

## Index redirects

When a layout has children, its index route (`/`) **redirects to the default child** via `beforeLoad`:

```ts
const indexRoute = createRoute({
  getParentRoute: () => parentRoute,
  path: '/',
  beforeLoad: () => { throw redirect({ to: '/parent/default-child' }); },
  component: () => null,
});
```

Established cases:
- `/settings` ‚Üí `/settings/profile`
- `/settings/organization` ‚Üí `/settings/organization/general`
- Future resource pages with multiple sub-pages

## Nested routes (`sub-pages/`)

When a page is `kind: 'layout'`, child routes live in `sub-pages/<child>/` as a full recursive copy of the same shape:

```
pages/organization/                       ‚Üí /organization
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ organization.route.tsx
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ organization.page.ts                  kind: 'layout', children: [...]
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ OrganizationLayout.tsx
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/...
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ sub-pages/
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ general/
    ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ general.route.tsx
    ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ general.page.ts
    ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ GeneralPage.tsx
    ‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/...
    ‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ...                           full island shape, recursively
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ...
```

## Dialog vs full page ‚Äî decision tree

When a sub-path exists under a page:

1. **Does it need a URL?**
   - YES ‚Üí either URL-driven dialog (sub-page renders null, parent shows dialog) or full page (sub-page renders Page UI)
   - NO ‚Üí local state (`useState` in parent's component)
2. **Page or dialog?**
   - **Page** when: complex, table-heavy, multi-step, mobile real estate matters, deep-link to detail context
   - **Dialog** when: form fits in modal, action stays in list context, transient
3. **Rule.** Everything between two `<page>.route.tsx` files belongs to the parent route's component.

## Component Promotion

Components start **colocated** with their page directory.

**Move to `shared/components/<Name>/` when:**
- Used by **2+ different page groups**
- Example: `StatusBadge` used in `pages/users/` AND `pages/organizations/` ‚Üí move to `src/shared/components/StatusBadge/`

**Never move to `shared/` when:**
- Only one page uses it (even if it looks "generic")
- It contains page-specific business logic

Promotion: copy to `shared/components/<Name>/`, update imports project-wide, delete the original.

## Shared Layer

```
src/shared/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ components/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ui/                                 shadcn primitives ‚Äî FLAT (button.tsx, card.tsx, ...)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ <Name>/{...}                        cross-page components ‚Äî folder-per-unit
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ ...
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ forms/<Name>/{...}                      cross-page forms
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ hooks/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ use<X>/                             cross-page custom hooks
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ useList/, useOne/                   standard CRUD hooks (Refine-style)
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ useCreate/, useUpdate/, useDelete/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ layouts/<Name>/{...}                    RootLayout, DashboardLayout, AuthLayout
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ store/                                  GLOBAL Zustand stores
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ useThemeStore/{...}
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ useUIStore/{...}
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ useOnboardingStore/{...}
```

## Core Layer

Framework-agnostic services, one subfolder per domain:

```
src/core/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ auth/                                   store, service, token, guards
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ http/                                   apiClient (axios), retry, queryClient
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ rbac/                                   policies + guards (requirePermission)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ tenancy/                                current tenant + permissions
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ data-provider/                          CRUD abstraction (REST adapter, mock adapter)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ resources/                              resource registry (central manifest)
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ analytics/                              PostHog
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ observability/                          Sentry, web vitals
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ config/                                 env schema, constants
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ errors/                                 AppError, HttpError, errorHandler
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ version/                                new-deployment detection
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ types/                                  branded types
```

## State Management

| Scope | Library | Location |
|-------|---------|----------|
| Server state | TanStack Query | `pages/<page>/hooks/use<X>/` or `shared/hooks/use{List,One,Create,Update,Delete}/` |
| Global client state | Zustand | `src/shared/store/use<X>Store/` (incl. `useTenantStore` ‚Äî current tenant) |
| Page-local client state | Zustand | `src/pages/<page>/store/use<X>Store/` *(rare)* |
| Component-local | `useState` / `useReducer` | Inline; extract reducer to `<Component>.reducer.ts` when complex |
| Form state | react-hook-form + Zod | Inside the form component |
| URL state | TanStack Router | `<page>.search.ts` (validateSearch schema) |

**All Zustand stores live in `src/shared/store/<X>Store/`** (folder-per-unit) ‚Äî `useAuthStore`, `useTenantStore`, `useThemeStore`, `useUIStore`, `useOnboardingStore`. There is no `core/<feature>/store.ts` pattern.

Cross-page API helpers (functions reused by both `pages/` and `shared/components/`) live in **`src/shared/api/`** (e.g., `shared/api/organization-api.ts`, `shared/api/tenancy-service.ts`).

Auth infrastructure (token storage, refresh timer, idle timeout, login/logout service, mocks) lives in **`src/shared/auth/`** ‚Äî not in core, because the HTTP client, error handler, shared components, and pages all need it.

**Rules:**
1. **Server state never goes in Zustand.** TanStack Query owns it.
2. **Page-local stores are an escape hatch** ‚Äî try `useState` ‚Üí `useReducer` ‚Üí URL search params ‚Üí shared store FIRST.
3. **Reducers live next to the component** that uses them. No `reducers/` directory.

## Tests

| Type | Location |
|------|----------|
| Unit (component, hook, form, util, store) | Colocated `<Name>.test.{ts,tsx}` next to source |
| Page integration (cross-component flow in this island) | `pages/<page>/__tests__/integration/` |
| E2E (full browser, cross-page) | `tests/e2e/` at project root (Playwright) |
| Load | `tests/load/` (k6) |

**No test file required for:**
- `<page>.route.tsx` (thin wrapper)
- `<page>.page.ts` (declarative manifest)
- `<page>.contracts.ts` (Zod ‚Äî type-checked at compile, exercised where used)
- `OVERVIEW.md`, `index.ts` (barrel re-exports)

## Import Rules

- Always use `@/` alias for imports from `src/`
- Always include `.ts`/`.tsx` extensions: `import { Button } from '@/shared/components/Button/index.ts'`
- Type-only imports: `import type { Org } from './<resource>.contracts.ts'`

**Dependency direction (one-way, with one documented exception):**

```
shared/components/ui ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ may import other ui primitives + lib
lib                  ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ may import from lib, core/types only
core                 ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ may import from lib, core/types (+ runtime trio, see below)
shared               ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ may import from core, lib, types
pages                ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ may import from shared, core, lib, types
app                  ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ may import from everything
```

**Runtime-trio exception (the only one):** the core kernel (`core/http`, `core/rbac`) may
import `shared/auth/`, `shared/errors/`, `useAuthStore`, and `useTenantStore`. Token
handling, error reporting, and permission checks are runtime services the kernel provides,
but that infrastructure is app-state- and SDK-dependent (Zustand, `@sentry/react`) so it
lives in `shared` (see Top-Level Layout). Core must never import any other `shared`
module. Enforced precisely by `no-restricted-imports` in `eslint.config.mjs`.

**Never:**
- Page imports another page (`pages/A/` ‚Üõ `pages/B/`)
- Shared imports from pages
- Core imports from pages, app, or any shared module outside the runtime trio
- UI primitives (`shared/components/ui/`) import anything internal except other ui primitives and `lib`

